# PRD — Capability Workspace: Drill-Down Navigation, Edit Behavior & Change Log
**Status:** Ready for Build  
**Last Updated:** March 2026  
**Feature Area:** Architect OS Pro Suite — Planning & Execution  
**Routes:** `/pro/planning/sprint-board` (overlay layers, no new routes)  
**Depends On:** Sprint Board Phase 1 complete, tiered initiative forms built  

---

## 1. Overview

The Sprint Board currently has two views — By Capability and By Initiative — that show aggregated counts and status. Neither provides a way to drill into the actual content without immediately triggering a creation form. This spec introduces a three-layer drill-down navigation system that lets founders review, navigate, and edit sprint content at every level of the hierarchy without leaving the Sprint Board.

The three layers:

| Layer | Accessed From | Shows |
|---|---|---|
| **Capability Workspace** | Clicking a capability card (By Capability view) | All initiatives within that capability area |
| **Initiative Workspace** | Clicking an initiative (from Capability Workspace or By Initiative view) | Full initiative detail, all milestones |
| **Milestone Expansion** | Clicking a milestone (from Initiative Workspace) | Already built — inline expansion. Keep as-is. |

All three layers open as overlays or slide-over panels — the Sprint Board remains visible and navigable in the background. No new routes are created.

---

## 2. Design Principle — View First, Edit by Choice

Every workspace opens in **read mode** by default. The founder sees what's there before they can change anything. Edit mode is activated deliberately — either by clicking an edit icon or an "Edit" label on a specific field. This distinction matters because:

- Founders will open these workspaces frequently just to review progress
- Accidental edits to locked or active sprint content should not happen passively
- The historical record (change log) should only capture intentional changes, not scroll-past hovers or misclicks

**Read mode:** All content visible, clean, no input fields. Fields display as styled text.  
**Edit mode:** Specific field or section becomes an editable input. Save and Cancel controls appear inline. The rest of the workspace remains in read mode.

