## 3. Layer 1 — Capability Workspace

### 3.1 Trigger

Clicking anywhere on a capability card in the **By Capability view** that is not the `+ Create Initiative` or `+ Add Initiative` CTA. The CTA itself still opens the tiered creation form directly.

### 3.2 Layout

A right-side slide-over panel occupying approximately 50-60% of the viewport width. The Sprint Board remains visible and partially interactive behind it. An overlay scrim dims the board slightly but does not block it entirely.

**Panel Header:**
- Capability name (large)
- Dimension tag
- Maturity score and stage status badge
- 3P column assignment: `Prioritize / Plant / Progressively Iterate` — displayed as a colored tag matching the column color
- Close control (×) top right

**Initiative List (body of panel):**

A scrollable list of all initiatives associated with this capability. Each initiative row shows:
- Initiative name
- Tier label (inherits from capability column — Prioritize / Plant / Iterate — but displayed as a subtle tag)
- Owner avatar(s)
- Milestone count (Prioritize only: `3 of 5 milestones complete`)
- Status indicator: `Not Started` / `In Progress` / `Complete` / `At Risk` / `Blocked`
- A right-facing chevron indicating the row is clickable

Clicking any initiative row opens the **Initiative Workspace** (Layer 2) — either sliding the capability panel further left or replacing it with the initiative panel. Preferred: slide-left so the user can see they've gone one level deeper and can navigate back.

**Empty state (no initiatives yet):**
A centered message: *"No initiatives added for this capability yet."* with a `+ Add Initiative` button below it. Clicking opens the appropriate tiered form for this capability's tier.

**Footer of panel:**
`+ Add Initiative` button — always present at the bottom of the initiative list regardless of existing count. Tapping opens the tiered creation form.

---

## 4. Layer 2 — Initiative Workspace

### 4.1 Trigger

- Clicking an initiative row inside the Capability Workspace
- Clicking an initiative card in the **By Initiative view** on the Sprint Board

### 4.2 Layout

The Initiative Workspace is the existing Initiative Detail modal (Image 5 from the build review). This is already well-built. The changes in this spec are:

1. It must be reachable from the Capability Workspace as a drill-down, not just as a standalone modal
2. It opens in **read mode** by default — not in an editable state
3. Edit mode is activatable on a field-by-field basis
4. The change log panel is added to the right-side metadata column

**Left panel (initiative content):**
- Initiative name — read mode default. Edit icon inline to activate edit mode for this field.
- Description / outcome statement — read mode. Edit icon.
- Sprint connection (why this sprint) — read mode. Edit icon. Prioritize only.
- Milestones section — existing implementation. Keep as-is.
- `+ Add Milestone` — always available at bottom of milestones section.

**Right panel (metadata):**
- Owner — read mode. Edit to change.
- Labels / capability links — read mode.
- Target Completion — read mode. Edit to change.
- Status selector (At Risk / On Track / Blocked) — this remains directly interactive. Status changes do not require entering edit mode — they are lightweight, frequent, and intentional by nature.
- **Change Log section** (new — see Section 6)
- Comments & Activity thread — existing implementation. Keep as-is.

### 4.3 Back Navigation

When reached from the Capability Workspace: a `← Back to [Capability Name]` link at the top of the panel. Returns to the Capability Workspace without closing it.

When reached directly from the By Initiative view: a `← Back to Sprint Board` link.

