## 6. Change Log

### 6.1 Purpose

A running record of every intentional edit to an initiative after creation. Lives inside the Initiative Workspace in the right panel, below the Status selector and above Comments & Activity.

### 6.2 Display

**Section label:** `CHANGE HISTORY`

A scrollable list of change entries in reverse chronological order (newest first). Each entry shows:
- What changed: field name + old value → new value
  Example: *"Outcome Statement updated"*
- Who changed it: owner avatar + name
- When: relative timestamp (e.g., "3 days ago") with full date on hover
- Optional context note if one was provided: displayed in a muted indented line below the entry

**Collapsed by default:** The section shows a count indicator — `3 changes` — and expands on click. This keeps the right panel clean for frequent viewers.

**Empty state:** If no changes have been made since creation, the section shows: *"No changes recorded yet."* Do not hide the section entirely — its presence signals to the founder that the platform is tracking evolution.

### 6.3 Data Table — `initiative_changes`

| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID | |
| `initiative_id` | UUID | FK to `sprint_initiatives` |
| `user_id` | UUID | Who made the change |
| `field_name` | Text | e.g., `outcome_statement` |
| `old_value` | Text | Previous field value |
| `new_value` | Text | Updated field value |
| `change_note` | Text | Optional — from change prompt |
| `created_at` | Timestamp | |

One row per field per save event. If a founder edits three fields in one session and saves each individually, three rows are created. If they edit and cancel, no row is created.

This table is append-only. No updates, no deletes. Historical record is permanent within the sprint record.

