## 7. Synthesis Staleness Flag

When a founder edits any outcome-level field on any initiative (outcome statement, sprint connection, what this unlocks, adjustment definition), the sprint posture synthesis — generated at sprint lock — may no longer accurately reflect the plan.

### 7.1 Flag Behavior

On save of any outcome-level field edit:
- Check whether a sprint posture synthesis exists for this quarter (`sprint_syntheses` table or equivalent)
- If yes: mark the synthesis record with `is_stale: true`
- Surface a non-blocking notice at the top of the Sprint Board (not inside the workspace): a slim banner reading *"Your sprint synthesis may no longer reflect your current plan. Regenerate?"* with a `Regenerate` link and a `Dismiss` link

**The banner:**
- Does not block any action
- Persists until the founder either regenerates or dismisses
- If dismissed, does not reappear unless another outcome-level edit is made
- If regenerated: triggers the synthesis generation flow again (same n8n webhook, same payload structure as original lock), replaces the synthesis content, sets `is_stale: false`

### 7.2 What Does Not Trigger the Flag

- Status changes
- Owner changes
- Target Completion changes
- Comments added
- Milestone status updates
- Labels changed
- Non-outcome field changes (constraints, time box, signal to watch)

These are operational updates. They do not change the strategic intent of the initiative and should not invalidate the synthesis.

