## 8. By Initiative View — Drill-Down Behavior

In the By Initiative view, capability cards are not present — the user is looking at a flat list of all initiatives organized by column. The drill-down behavior is simpler:

Clicking any initiative card (collapsed or expanded) opens the **Initiative Workspace** directly. No Capability Workspace layer in between — the user is already past that level.

The Initiative Workspace opened from By Initiative view has `← Back to Sprint Board` navigation rather than `← Back to [Capability Name]`.

Everything else — read mode, edit mode, change log, staleness flag — behaves identically.

---

## 9. Capability Workspace — Additional States

### 9.1 Capability with No Initiatives

Empty state as described in Section 3.2. The panel still opens — it just shows the empty state rather than a list.

### 9.2 Capability at Volume Guardrail

If a Prioritize capability already has two initiatives and the volume guardrail has been surfaced, the `+ Add Initiative` button in the Capability Workspace footer shows the soft notice inline rather than opening the form immediately: *"You have 2 initiatives for this capability. Adding more may stretch your sprint capacity."* with `Add Anyway` and `Cancel` options.

### 9.3 Post-Lock Editing

After the sprint is locked, all edit icons remain present but fields carry a subtle indicator: `Locked Sprint — editing will be versioned`. This is not a barrier — it's a notice. Editing still works. The change log captures all post-lock edits. The staleness flag applies as above.

